<dl id="n41087f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41087f">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41087f"> 87(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> gai, gai</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">TOUJOURS GAI / <font size="-1">RONDE BRETONNE</font>: Toujours <mark>ga&icirc;, ga&icirc;,</mark> toujours ga&icirc;ment; / Berg&egrave;re, allons ga&icirc;, ga&icirc;, / Berg&egrave;re, allons ga&icirc;ment. [EVER CHEERFUL / <font size="-1">BRETON ROUND DANCE</font>: Ever cheerful, cheerful, ever cheerfully, / Shepherdess, let us go cheerful, cheerful, / Shepherdess, let us go cheerfully. <small> V.-F. Verrimst, <a name="VFVR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#VFVR"><cite title="source">Rondes et Chansons Populaires</cite></a> (1886) 87</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: This refrain occurs throughout the song. <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c06189c" href="c06all.htm#c06189c">VI.C.06:189(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
